Vaneza Pitynski https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vaneza_Pitynski 0 Vaneza Leza Pitynski (born September 1, 1988 in Whittier, California, USA) is an American actress, singer, voice actress, fashion blogger, and digital manager of German-Russian-Puerto Rican descent. She is best known for her roles as Lorena Garcia on Nickelodeon's The Brothers Garcia and Skye in Fatherhood. In 2001, Vaneza released her only album, Mr. Guapo through DDP Music when she was twelve years old and was also met with positive reviews from critics. She released a CD single in 2003 for All I Wanna Do is Dance. She quit acting in 2005 after losing interest in it, having begun professionally in 1998, then attended college at the University of Southern California from 2006 to 2010, majoring in theater. She is currently a fashion blogger and works as a digital manager.
